<li id="cite_note-31"><b><a href="#cite_ref-31" title="">^</a></b> Timpani are also called Kettledrums in English and Pauken in German. Two players are required: one for each pair of timpani.</li>
<li id="cite_note-32"><b><a href="#cite_ref-32" title="">^</a></b> A tam-tam is also called a gong in English and is a tamtam in German.</li>
<li id="cite_note-33"><b><a href="#cite_ref-33" title="">^</a></b> Six harps play together in the final scene. See Dover, at page 309.</li>
<li id="cite_note-34"><b><a href="#cite_ref-34" title="">^</a></b> Richard Wagner, <i>Siegfried in Full Score</i>. 1983: Dover Publications, Inc., New York. Referred to below as the "Dover Score".</li>
<li id="cite_note-35"><b><a href="#cite_ref-35" title="">^</a></b> Wagner's score divides the violin section into 16 First Violins and 16 Second Violins.</li>
